Revert "Add ARM64 filter support."

This reverts commit 33e03bdda9b86bef7f61e521744f109af1b71951.

Due to the on-going issues with the XZ Utils backdooring, to be
100% on the safe-side I am reverting all PRs from that project.

This is the only PR since I wrote the original code in 2010.

It can be re-added at a later date if or when more details about
the extent and start of backdooring come to light.

mksquashfs: abort if pseudo file defs will be ignored

If someone creates a pseudo-file where one of the intermediate
directories in the pathname doesn't exist, it will be ignored.

Similarly, if one of the intermediate directories isn't a
directory in the filesystem, it will also be ignored.

This commit checks for these instances and aborts.

Signed-off-by: Phillip Lougher <phillip@squashfs.org.uk>

mksquashfs: always assign pathname to pseudo entry

Always assign pathname to pseudo entries, rather than just
leaf-component entries and/or those with a pseudo xattr.

This first ensures intermediate pseudo entries (i.e. non
leaf-components) have a pathname, and second it fixes
a potential memory leak introduced last year with pseudo
xattrs.

Signed-off-by: Phillip Lougher <phillip@squashfs.org.uk>
